Dad, what are you writing?

176
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:33,491
Maybe I'm spending too much
of my time starting up clubs -

177
00:12:33,578 --> 00:12:35,578
- and putting on plays.

178
00:12:35,621 --> 00:12:37,752
That's possible.

179
00:12:37,796 --> 00:12:41,406
- I should probably be trying
harder to score chicks.

180
00:12:41,492 --> 00:12:44,579
That's the only thing
anybody really cares about.

181
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:47,537
It's not my forte, unfortunately.

182
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,755
It'll happen, Max. It's just...

183
00:12:49,841 --> 00:12:52,408
You're like one of those
clipper ship captains.

184
00:12:52,494 --> 00:12:54,756
You're married to the sea.

185
00:12:54,843 --> 00:12:56,756
Yes, that's true.

186
00:12:56,843 --> 00:13:00,408
But I've been out to sea
for a long time.

187
00:13:06,714 --> 00:13:09,541
- Hello.
- Hi.

188
00:13:17,412 --> 00:13:19,847
I like your hat.

189
00:13:19,934 --> 00:13:22,717
Oh, thank you.

190
00:13:22,804 --> 00:13:25,892
You're a teacher here,
aren't you?

191
00:13:27,979 --> 00:13:30,066
And this is your first year
at Rushmore, I take it.

192
00:13:30,110 --> 00:13:32,241
Uh-huh.

193
00:13:32,283 --> 00:13:35,676
And how long have you been a smoker,
if you don't mind me asking?

194
00:13:35,719 --> 00:13:39,155
Well, let's see now.
H- How old are you?

195
00:13:39,242 --> 00:13:41,546
Fifteen.

196
00:13:41,634 --> 00:13:44,547
- Since I was your age.
- You're kidding.

197
00:13:44,591 --> 00:13:46,504
You should quit.

198
00:13:46,591 --> 00:13:49,287
You're right.

199
00:13:49,331 --> 00:13:51,722
And I should mind my own business.

200
00:13:58,158 --> 00:14:00,594
Where did you go
to school, by the way?

201
00:14:00,637 --> 00:14:02,507
- Harvard.
- Really?

202
00:14:02,594 --> 00:14:04,507
That's a coincidence.

203
00:14:04,595 --> 00:14:07,638
My top schools where I want
to apply to are Oxford and the Sorbonne.

204
00:14:07,725 --> 00:14:09,683
My safety's Harvard.

205
00:14:09,726 --> 00:14:13,509
- That's very ambitious.
- Thank you.

206
00:14:13,596 --> 00:14:15,727
What do you want to study?

207
00:14:15,814 --> 00:14:18,857
Well... I haven't
decided for sure, -

208
00:14:18,945 --> 00:14:23,685
- but probably a double major
in mathematics and premed.

209
00:14:23,772 --> 00:14:25,729
What was your major?

210
00:14:25,773 --> 00:14:30,773
I didn't have a major, but my thesis
was on Latin American economic policy.

211
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:31,991
Oh, that's interesting.

212
00:14:31,991 --> 00:14:34,731
Did you hear they're not going
to teach Latin here anymore?

213
00:14:34,774 --> 00:14:37,862
This was more like Central America.

214
00:14:37,948 --> 00:14:40,905
Oh, Central America
and whatnot. Hmm.

215
00:14:40,949 --> 00:14:43,559
But moving on:
They're gonna cancel Latin.

216
00:14:43,646 --> 00:14:46,907
They've got
to make room for Japanese.

217
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:51,081
That's a shame because all the Romance
languages were based on Latin.

218
00:14:51,125 --> 00:14:53,124
Yeah, they are,
aren't they?

219
00:14:53,212 --> 00:14:55,865
Nihilo sanctum estne?

220
00:14:55,952 --> 00:14:59,735
What's that?
Oh, it's Latin, isn't it?

221
00:14:59,822 --> 00:15:01,909
What does that mean?

222
00:15:01,996 --> 00:15:04,997
Is nothing sacred?

223
00:15:11,738 --> 00:15:15,346
Sic transit gloria.
Glory fades.

224
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:18,173
I'm Max Fischer.

225
00:15:18,261 --> 00:15:20,783
- Hi.
- Hi.

226
00:15:25,652 --> 00:15:28,349
- Come on, come on. File out.
- Sign here, please.

227
00:15:28,437 --> 00:15:30,480
- Sic transit gloria.
- All right, all right.

228
00:15:38,264 --> 00:15:40,395
In summation,
I have only one question:

229
00:15:40,438 --> 00:15:43,265
Is Latin dead?

230
00:15:48,004 --> 00:15:51,528
Why don't you just piss off,
Fischer, you dotty skid mark?

231
00:15:51,614 --> 00:15:53,527
Was that Latin?

232
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:03,182
Never in my wildest
imagination -

233
00:16:03,225 --> 00:16:06,660
- did I ever dream I would have
sons like these.

234
00:16:09,096 --> 00:16:11,357
What's your dad do, Max?

235
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:16,532
He's a neurosurgeon...
at, uh, St. Joseph's Hospital.

236
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:19,532
Personally, I could never see myself
cutting open somebody's brain, -

237
00:16:19,576 --> 00:16:22,575
- but he seems to enjoy it.

238
00:16:22,619 --> 00:16:25,707
Oh, no, no, no. I got this one.

239
00:16:27,926 --> 00:16:30,186
So you were in Vietnam,
if I'm not mistaken?

240
00:16:30,186 --> 00:16:31,013
Yeah.

241
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:35,188
Were you in the shit?

242
00:16:35,274 --> 00:16:37,884
Yeah, I was in the shit.

243
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:40,450
See you Sunday, Mr. Blume.

244
00:16:40,536 --> 00:16:43,188
- All right.
- What's on Sunday?

245
00:16:43,276 --> 00:16:46,059
Oh, that's right.
The twins' birthday party.

246
00:16:46,103 --> 00:16:49,843
Do you want to come?

247
00:16:49,929 --> 00:16:53,364
I'd love to, except I've already got
a previous obligation to attend to.

248
00:16:53,451 --> 00:16:56,756
Yeah. Thanks for
the invitation, though.

249
00:16:58,627 --> 00:17:01,236
Come work for me.

250
00:17:01,279 --> 00:17:06,323
- What do you mean?
- I mean, I-I-I could use someone like you.

251
00:17:07,715 --> 00:17:10,150
Look, I may not be rich, Mr. Blume.

252
00:17:10,238 --> 00:17:13,281
My father may only be
a doctor, but we manage.

253
00:17:13,325 --> 00:17:16,847
- One-twelves!
- Excuse me, Mr. Blume. Nice talking to you.

254
00:17:18,456 --> 00:17:20,805
You're on the team?

255
00:17:20,891 --> 00:17:22,806
I'm an alternate.

256
00:17:24,414 --> 00:17:26,848
How you doin'? Good to see you again.

257
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:39,286
Whoa. Neat.

258
00:18:56,561 --> 00:19:00,041
Miss Cross?

259
00:19:00,128 --> 00:19:03,302
I thought I'd just let you know
as per our conversation, the other day...

260
00:19:03,389 --> 00:19:06,129
- Latin?
- Right. The Romance languages.

261
00:19:06,215 --> 00:19:08,998
- Well, I gave a little speech.
- I heard about this.

262
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,607
Oh, you did?

263
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:14,304
I understand you made a
very convincing argument.

264
00:19:14,391 --> 00:19:17,130
I just thought you'd be pleased -

265
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:19,826
- to hear they're gonna
continue the Latin program.

266
00:19:19,913 --> 00:19:22,000
I'm very impressed.

267
00:19:22,044 --> 00:19:25,001
Well, thank you very much.

268
00:19:25,089 --> 00:19:27,349
Hey, you need an assistant?

269
00:19:27,393 --> 00:19:30,002
Do we get to have an
assistant around here?

270
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,176
No, I doubt it.

271
00:19:31,219 --> 00:19:33,655
I'm on scholarship, though...
academic scholarship, -

272
00:19:33,743 --> 00:19:36,351
- so I get to do odd jobs and...

273
00:19:36,395 --> 00:19:39,004
Say, how did you decide
to teach at Rushmore?

274
00:19:39,091 --> 00:19:41,004
My husband went here.

275
00:19:43,439 --> 00:19:48,006
I, uh... I didn't know
you were married.

276
00:19:48,092 --> 00:19:50,005
Well, he's dead now.

277
00:19:50,093 --> 00:19:52,006
So I'm not, actually.

278
00:19:52,093 --> 00:19:54,180
When did he die?

279
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:56,181
Last year.

280
00:19:57,747 --> 00:19:59,703
My mother's dead.

281
00:20:00,790 --> 00:20:02,704
I'm sorry to hear that.

282
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:05,704
She died when I was seven.

283
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:08,879
I guess we both have
dead people in our families.

284
00:20:13,445 --> 00:20:15,880
What's going on in here?

285
00:20:17,968 --> 00:20:20,272
These were just born.

286
00:20:22,447 --> 00:20:26,230
I don't want alloys. I want steel.

287
00:20:26,273 --> 00:20:29,883
I don't give a rat's ass what he says.

288
00:20:31,970 --> 00:20:34,232
Steel, Harry.

289
00:20:34,318 --> 00:20:37,188
So you've changed your
mind, and you want the job?

290
00:20:37,797 --> 00:20:40,233
No, but I've got an idea,
and I need some money.

291
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:42,886
What Rushmore
needs is an aquarium -

292
00:20:42,972 --> 00:20:45,582
- a first-class aquarium...
where the scientists can lecture -

293
00:20:45,668 --> 00:20:48,755
- and the students can observe the
marine life in its natural habitat.

294
00:20:48,799 --> 00:20:50,582
I don't know. What
do you think, Ernie?

295
00:20:50,582 --> 00:20:51,540
An aquarium?

296
00:20:51,626 --> 00:20:52,888
What kind of fish?

297
00:20:52,888 --> 00:20:55,584
Barracudas, stingrays,
electric eel, trout, -

298
00:20:55,670 --> 00:20:58,584
- hammerheads, piranhas,
giant squid, octopi...

299
00:20:58,671 --> 00:20:59,975
Piranhas? Really?

300
00:20:59,975 --> 00:21:02,672
Yes, I'm talking to
a guy in South America.

301
00:21:02,716 --> 00:21:04,455
What'd Guggenheim say?

302
00:21:04,455 --> 00:21:06,195
Nothing. I felt I
should go to you first.

303
00:21:06,281 --> 00:21:08,368
Why?

304
00:21:08,455 --> 00:21:12,194
Because at this moment, I feel the
best strategy is to keep it low profile.

305
00:21:12,282 --> 00:21:15,196
The more preparation work I can do,
the stronger our case will be -

306
00:21:15,283 --> 00:21:18,240
- when we take it to the administration.
- How much money do you want?

307
00:21:18,327 --> 00:21:22,545
Thirty-five thousand dollars,
for the initial plans.

308
00:21:31,938 --> 00:21:33,851
I'll give you 2.500.

309
00:21:33,937 --> 00:21:35,982
Okay.

310
00:22:24,296 --> 00:22:26,253
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

311
00:23:02,737 --> 00:23:06,347
- Max.
- Mm-hmm?

312
00:23:06,434 --> 00:23:09,999
- Can I ask you something?
- Sure.

313
00:23:10,087 --> 00:23:14,435
Has it ever crossed your mind
that you're far too young for me?

314
00:23:19,436 --> 00:23:23,871
It crossed my mind that you might
consider that a possibility. Yeah.

315
00:23:23,959 --> 00:23:26,046
Quite apart from the fact
that you're a student...

316
00:23:26,089 --> 00:23:29,047
I'm not trying to pressure you
into anything, Miss Cross.

317
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:30,916
I'm surprised you
brought it up so bluntly.

318
00:23:30,916 --> 00:23:32,090
I just want to make sure...

319
00:23:35,786 --> 00:23:38,787
- We've become friends, haven't we?
- Yes.

320
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,831
Good.

321
00:23:40,875 --> 00:23:43,222
And, um... -

322
00:23:43,266 --> 00:23:46,527
- the... the truth is, neither one of us
has the slightest idea -

323
00:23:46,615 --> 00:23:48,572
- where this relationship is going.

324
00:23:48,658 --> 00:23:52,443
- We can't predict the future.
- We don't have a relationship, Max.

325
00:23:52,529 --> 00:23:55,399
- But we're friends.
- Yes, and that's all we're going to be.

326
00:23:55,443 --> 00:23:58,051
That's all I meant by "relationship".

327
00:23:58,138 --> 00:24:00,139
You want me to grab a dictionary?

328
00:24:00,182 --> 00:24:03,661
No, I just want to make sure
that we understand each other.

329
00:24:03,749 --> 00:24:05,662
I understand.

330
00:24:05,748 --> 00:24:08,662
You're not attracted to me.

331
00:24:08,749 --> 00:24:11,098
C'est la vie.

332
00:24:11,184 --> 00:24:14,360
Max, you're 15 years old.

333
00:24:14,402 --> 00:24:16,968
Attraction doesn't enter into it.

334
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:19,664
If you say so.

335
00:24:19,751 --> 00:24:22,012
Look, all I'm getting at is that -

336
00:24:23,926 --> 00:24:27,535
- that I've never met anyone like you.

337
00:24:29,275 --> 00:24:31,884
So you can take that
for whatever it's worth.

338
00:24:34,275 --> 00:24:38,711
I think I can safely say
I've never met anyone like you either.

339
00:24:42,277 --> 00:24:44,451
You haven't, have you?

340
00:24:46,844 --> 00:24:49,452
Want to shake hands?

341
00:24:50,496 --> 00:24:52,887
I'm glad we had this conversation.

342
00:24:52,975 --> 00:24:54,888
So am I.

343
00:24:56,757 --> 00:24:58,541
I can't wear a wire.
They're feeling me up every day.

344
00:24:58,629 --> 00:25:01,716
Oh, come on, Frank.
You'll have complete protection.

345
00:25:01,802 --> 00:25:03,672
Yeah, I've heard that one before.

346
00:25:03,716 --> 00:25:05,803
- I gotta put a dime in the meter.
- Sit down, Frank.

347
00:25:05,890 --> 00:25:09,152
Joe, go put a dime in the meter
for Officer Serpico.

348
00:25:09,239 --> 00:25:11,457
Look, Serpico, if you agree
to testify in open court...

349
00:25:11,457 --> 00:25:12,066
No!

350
00:25:12,152 --> 00:25:15,892
- No, what?
- No, I'm not gonna testify.

351
00:25:15,978 --> 00:25:17,979
Go, go, go.

352
00:25:18,066 --> 00:25:22,024
I'll expect your gun
and your badge on my desk...

353
00:25:22,068 --> 00:25:24,502
- Promise me one thing, O'Reilly.
- Name it.

354
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:26,851
That you're gonna follow this thing
all the way to the end -

355
00:25:26,938 --> 00:25:28,894
- of the line... where I got to be.

356
00:25:28,938 --> 00:25:31,199
So help me God.

357
00:25:31,243 --> 00:25:33,853
- Someone coming out of the building.
- I've got something!

358
00:25:33,939 --> 00:25:36,374
- Wait. This could be it.
- There's action across the street.

359
00:25:36,417 --> 00:25:39,157
- Yeah, it's him.
- It's Snowman.

360
00:25:41,505 --> 00:25:43,681
- He's getting on the "L" train!
- Take him!

361
00:25:45,985 --> 00:25:48,202
- What happened to the cannoli line?
- Max...

362
00:25:48,290 --> 00:25:49,289
You're supposed to say, -

363
00:25:49,289 --> 00:25:51,376
- "Forget about it, Sanchez.
The old man likes his cannolis."

364
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:54,030
Look, I made a mistake, all right?
It didn't make any difference anyway.

365
00:25:54,117 --> 00:25:56,856
Hey, I'm letting it go,
but don't say it doesn't matter.

366
00:25:56,944 --> 00:25:59,552
- Every line matters.
- Get off my back!

367
00:25:59,596 --> 00:26:01,553
Don't fuck with my play!

368
00:26:01,639 --> 00:26:03,640
- You fucking cocksucker...
- Hey, break it up. Break it up.

369
00:26:03,726 --> 00:26:06,075
I'm gonna kill you.

370
00:26:13,077 --> 00:26:15,642
Max. Max.

371
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,256
I thought the acting tonight
was excellent.

372
00:26:42,256 --> 00:26:43,169
Thanks.

373
00:26:43,256 --> 00:26:45,691
Well, it was better in rehearsals.

374
00:26:45,778 --> 00:26:48,693
I'll catch up with you later, Dad.
I got a dinner to go to.

375
00:26:48,779 --> 00:26:52,214
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. Cast and crew only.

376
00:26:52,258 --> 00:26:55,345
- Oh. You need some money?
- No, Dad.

377
00:26:58,432 --> 00:27:01,042
- Well, how was the slap?
- It was good.

378
00:27:01,129 --> 00:27:04,652
- There he is. Max, that was great.
- I'm so glad you could come.

379
00:27:04,694 --> 00:27:07,652
I want you to meet a friend of mine.
Peter Flynn, Max Fischer.

380
00:27:07,695 --> 00:27:10,130
- Hi.
- Who's this guy?

381
00:27:11,566 --> 00:27:12,435
Peter.

382
00:27:12,435 --> 00:27:16,479
I really liked your
play. It was really cool.

383
00:27:16,567 --> 00:27:20,479
- Yeah.
- What happened to your nose?

384
00:27:20,567 --> 00:27:23,829
- I got punched in the face.
- Oh, boy.

385
00:27:23,916 --> 00:27:27,308
- What's your excuse?
- Hey, author.

386
00:27:27,351 --> 00:27:29,308
- How you doing?
- Nice job.

387
00:27:29,351 --> 00:27:31,482
- Thank you.
- Gonna get to meet your dad tonight?

388
00:27:31,569 --> 00:27:33,483
Oh, no. The old man's on call.

389
00:27:33,570 --> 00:27:35,527
Mr. Blume, I'd like you
to meet Miss Cross -

390
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:38,527
- and I didn't catch this young
gentleman's name.

391
00:27:38,614 --> 00:27:42,528
I like your nurse's uniform, guy.

392
00:27:42,571 --> 00:27:44,659
These are O.R. Scrubs.

393
00:27:44,746 --> 00:27:49,181
"O.R." they?

394
00:27:49,268 --> 00:27:52,660
Well, they're totally
inappropriate for the occasion.

395
00:27:52,747 --> 00:27:54,139
Well, I didn't know
we were going to dinner.

396
00:27:54,181 --> 00:27:57,357
That's because you weren't invited.

397
00:27:57,444 --> 00:27:58,618
Take it easy, Max.

398
00:27:58,618 --> 00:28:00,836
You were the one that
ordered him a whiskey and soda.

399
00:28:00,879 --> 00:28:02,835
So what's wrong with that?

400
00:28:02,923 --> 00:28:07,968
I can write a hit play. Why can't I have
a little drink to unwind myself?

401
00:28:09,924 --> 00:28:12,316
So, tell me, curly,
how do you know Miss Cross?

402
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,620
- We went to Harvard together.
- Oh, that's great.

403
00:28:14,708 --> 00:28:16,664
I wrote a hit play
and directed it.

404
00:28:16,707 --> 00:28:18,665
So I'm not sweating it either.

405
00:28:18,709 --> 00:28:20,666
Can we get a check, please?

406
00:28:20,709 --> 00:28:22,970
- What do you think you're doing?
- Getting the check.

407
00:28:23,057 --> 00:28:24,970
No, you're not. Excuse me.

408
00:28:25,057 --> 00:28:27,144
I just want to thank you
for accommodating us.

409
00:28:27,232 --> 00:28:29,320
You see, we only thought
we were going to be three, -

410
00:28:29,406 --> 00:28:32,841
- but, uh, someone invited
himself along, so I apologize.

411
00:28:32,885 --> 00:28:35,886
- Quite all right, sir. Very well.
- Okay.

412
00:28:35,929 --> 00:28:37,929
You're being rude, Max.

413
00:28:38,016 --> 00:28:39,930
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

414
00:28:40,016 --> 00:28:42,974
No, I'm not. I'm just trying to figure out
why you brought this gentleman to my play -

415
00:28:43,061 --> 00:28:45,844
- and my dinner,
which was invitation only.

416
00:28:45,930 --> 00:28:48,626
Would you like me to
pass you the creamer, Doc?

417
00:28:48,626 --> 00:28:49,757
Yes, please.

418
00:28:49,844 --> 00:28:53,845
- What is wrong with you?
- What is wrong with you?

419
00:28:53,933 --> 00:28:56,498
You hurt my feelings!
This night was important to me!

420
00:28:56,585 --> 00:28:59,934
How did I hurt your feelings?

421
00:28:59,976 --> 00:29:04,370
Oh, my God!
I wrote a hit play!

422
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:10,457
And I'm in love with you.

423
00:29:19,676 --> 00:29:21,633
Put that a little bit there.

424
00:29:41,072 --> 00:29:44,507
- Hi.
- Were you hiding over there?

425
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:47,986
Uh, I didn't want
to disrupt class.

426
00:29:49,552 --> 00:29:51,509
What's that you're painting?

427
00:29:51,595 --> 00:29:54,856
That's a... a jellyfish.

428
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:57,508
What can I do for you, Mr. Blume?

429
00:29:57,596 --> 00:30:00,032
Max wants to talk to you.

430
00:30:00,075 --> 00:30:03,858
- What for?
- To apologize, I think.

431
00:30:03,902 --> 00:30:06,336
Should we talk over here?

432
00:30:07,902 --> 00:30:09,860
He sent you?

433
00:30:09,947 --> 00:30:12,034
Yeah.

434
00:30:12,078 --> 00:30:14,339
Are you his messenger?

435
00:30:14,425 --> 00:30:17,861
No, I'm his friend.

436
00:30:17,947 --> 00:30:22,514
You were right.
I should not have allowed him to drink.

437
00:30:24,253 --> 00:30:27,863
I don't think
I should see Max anymore.

438
00:30:27,949 --> 00:30:29,950
Well, he's not gonna like
the sound of that.

439
00:30:29,994 --> 00:30:33,212
No. No, I know, but...

440
00:30:33,298 --> 00:30:36,560
I think I let him
get too attached.

441
00:30:36,603 --> 00:30:38,690
What do you think?

442
00:30:38,778 --> 00:30:42,039
Well, I think
you did your best.

443
00:30:45,780 --> 00:30:48,214
Tell him I'm sorry.

444
00:30:53,650 --> 00:30:55,564
Okay.

445
00:30:57,477 --> 00:31:00,391
What is your first name?

446
00:31:00,477 --> 00:31:04,521
Rosemary. What's yours?

447
00:31:04,565 --> 00:31:06,653
Herman.

448
00:31:11,088 --> 00:31:13,131
He wrote you a letter.

449
00:31:13,305 --> 00:31:14,828
Dear Miss Cross,

450
00:31:14,914 --> 00:31:17,350
I would like to take this opportunity
to formally apologize -

451
00:31:17,437 --> 00:31:19,872
- for the events of the night
of the 23rd.

452
00:31:19,916 --> 00:31:22,699
I'm not accustomed
to drinking alcohol.

453
00:31:22,742 --> 00:31:27,003
Please do me the service of coming to the
unveiling of a new venture I've undertaken.

454
00:31:27,047 --> 00:31:29,526
I hope you will attend,
if possible.

455
00:31:29,614 --> 00:31:33,396
I remain your friend, Max Fischer.

456
00:31:40,441 --> 00:31:42,877
Cut the music and no more pictures.

457
00:31:42,963 --> 00:31:44,876
- What time is it, Alan?
- 1:15.

458
00:31:44,964 --> 00:31:47,877
Excuse me, gentlemen.
Hey, lay off the chips, Buchan.

459
00:31:47,964 --> 00:31:49,877
Did you see her?

460
00:31:49,965 --> 00:31:52,226
- She's not here.
- Well, go check her classroom.

461
00:31:52,270 --> 00:31:53,922
Shall I go ahead and
take care of this tree?

462
00:31:53,922 --> 00:31:54,705
Let's wait a few minutes.

463
00:31:54,792 --> 00:31:57,400
- What's going on here, Maxie?
- Oh, hey, Coach Beck. Good to see you.

464
00:31:57,444 --> 00:31:59,401
This is where we're
putting in the new aquarium.

465
00:31:59,445 --> 00:32:01,403
I'm in charge of the committee,
if you can believe it.

466
00:32:01,445 --> 00:32:04,011
This is my baseball diamond.

467
00:32:04,055 --> 00:32:08,229
Yeah, I know, and I believe
it's being relocated a few feet over.

468
00:32:08,316 --> 00:32:10,663
Is it true the aquarium
will have piranhas?

469
00:32:10,751 --> 00:32:12,230
Where did you hear that?

470
00:32:12,230 --> 00:32:14,666
- My source indicated
that it was a possibility.

471
00:32:14,752 --> 00:32:17,492
Yes, it's true, but piranhas
are a very tricky species.

472
00:32:17,578 --> 00:32:20,361
- Max?
- Excuse me, George.

473
00:32:20,405 --> 00:32:22,362
- Bad news.
- What's the story?

474
00:32:22,405 --> 00:32:24,668
- She had a substitute teacher today.
- Why?

475
00:32:24,754 --> 00:32:26,058
I guess she got sick.

476
00:32:26,058 --> 00:32:28,189
You know she's not sick.
Give me the phone.

477
00:32:32,277 --> 00:32:34,537
Janet, Max Fischer.
Is Mr. Blume there?

478
00:32:34,582 --> 00:32:38,017
Well, where is he?

479
00:32:38,104 --> 00:32:40,453
Goddamn it.
He's supposed to be here.

480
00:32:40,539 --> 00:32:42,714
- I don't give a shit
about the barracudas, -

481
00:32:42,757 --> 00:32:45,714
- but, fuck it, I'm building it anyway.

482
00:32:45,758 --> 00:32:48,019
Max!

483
00:32:48,106 --> 00:32:50,715
Where are those damn chain saws
coming from?

484
00:32:50,759 --> 00:32:52,715
- He's right over there!
- Max!

485
00:32:52,802 --> 00:32:54,890
- Max!
- Oh, hello, Dr. Guggenheim.

486
00:32:54,933 --> 00:32:57,543
- What the hell do you think you're doing?
- We're having a fund-raiser for the...

487
00:32:57,630 --> 00:33:00,195
Turn that damn thing off!

488
00:33:00,283 --> 00:33:02,152
Tell me this isn't happening.

