01:19:40,320 --> 01:19:43,494
This is gonna be exciting.
My son Max wrote it.

993
01:19:43,581 --> 01:19:47,016
Oh, boy, I gotta call the hospital.

994
01:19:47,060 --> 01:19:49,539
Excuse me. Are you
Mrs. Whitney, the English teacher?

995
01:19:49,583 --> 01:19:50,452
Yes.

996
01:19:50,452 --> 01:19:52,453
Hi, I'm William Yang,
Margaret Yang's father.

997
01:19:52,539 --> 01:19:54,453
- This is my wife, Lucille.
- Nice to meet you.

998
01:19:54,540 --> 01:19:56,583
- Hello.
- That's kid's gonna burn this place down.

999
01:19:56,671 --> 01:19:57,975
You better believe it.

1000
01:19:57,975 --> 01:20:00,279
Well, the plans were never
formally submitted to the city.

1001
01:20:00,323 --> 01:20:02,281
- Were they supposed to be?
- I assume so.

1002
01:20:02,367 --> 01:20:04,933
- Too late now.
- Officers Brooks and Donovan -

1003
01:20:05,021 --> 01:20:07,282
- requesting additional units
at Grover Cleveland High School.

1004
01:20:07,368 --> 01:20:09,281
- Units responding identify.
- A program.

1005
01:20:09,369 --> 01:20:13,196
Let me look at that.
Turn it, turn it.

1006
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:15,196
That's enough.

1007
01:20:17,414 --> 01:20:20,197
- Excuse me. Right here.
- Thanks.

1008
01:20:24,154 --> 01:20:26,068
Hi, Herman.

1009
01:20:29,807 --> 01:20:32,372
Looks like Max
pulled a fast one on us.

1010
01:20:40,331 --> 01:20:42,983
Thank you very much.

1011
01:20:43,071 --> 01:20:47,072
I don't usually do this,
but this play means a lot to me, -

1012
01:20:47,159 --> 01:20:49,420
- and I wanted to make a dedication.

1013
01:20:49,506 --> 01:20:53,159
So, I'll just say that this play
is dedicated to the memory of my mother,

1014
01:20:53,246 --> 01:20:56,377
Eloise Fischer, -

1015
01:20:56,420 --> 01:20:59,466
- and to Edward Appleby,
a friend of a friend.

1016
01:20:59,552 --> 01:21:03,161
Also, you'll find a pair
of safety glasses and some earplugs -

1017
01:21:03,248 --> 01:21:05,161
- underneath your seats.

1018
01:21:05,249 --> 01:21:08,815
Please feel free to use them.
Thank you very much.

1019
01:21:15,511 --> 01:21:17,598
Bravo Company, this is Tango 7.
Do you copy?

1020
01:21:17,685 --> 01:21:21,383
We order the military forces
of the United States to take action...

1021
01:21:21,469 --> 01:21:23,991
This is a different kind of war.

1022
01:21:24,079 --> 01:21:27,382
We are making progress,
progress, progress, progress.

1023
01:21:38,602 --> 01:21:41,213
How long you been
in country, soldier?

1024
01:21:41,255 --> 01:21:43,560
I ain't even here, Sergeant.

1025
01:21:43,604 --> 01:21:45,560
I'm in Cheyenne, Wyoming.

1026
01:21:45,604 --> 01:21:48,213
Right on, brother.

1027
01:21:50,387 --> 01:21:53,084
Hoo. Hoo-hoo.

1028
01:21:55,171 --> 01:21:58,780
Let's rock, Esposito!
I repeat, let's rock!

1029
01:21:58,867 --> 01:22:01,519
Let's rock and roll!

1030
01:22:36,004 --> 01:22:37,918
Fischer!

1031
01:22:40,310 --> 01:22:42,440
I'm okay.
Go, go, go, go.

1032
01:22:42,527 --> 01:22:44,919
- Damn it!
- Take it easy, Dirk.

1033
01:22:45,006 --> 01:22:47,093
- How much time do we got, Wood?
- Two minutes.

1034
01:22:47,180 --> 01:22:48,833
All right, bring me some more
ketchup very quickly, please.

1035
01:22:48,833 --> 01:22:49,703
Effects!

1036
01:22:49,790 --> 01:22:53,138
- This is gonna look stupid.
- No, it's not. It's gonna look real.

1037
01:23:10,401 --> 01:23:13,969
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1038
01:23:14,055 --> 01:23:16,099
Hold this one too, okay?

1039
01:23:19,491 --> 01:23:23,753
So, what do you think
of Max's latest opus?

1040
01:23:25,145 --> 01:23:27,058
It's good.

1041
01:23:29,666 --> 01:23:32,666
But let's hope
it's got a happy ending.

1042
01:23:50,279 --> 01:23:54,888
- Adis, Esposito.
- Adis, Sarge.

1043
01:23:54,976 --> 01:23:58,889
Say a prayer for Surf Boy,
wherever he is.

1044
01:23:58,977 --> 01:24:03,021
Semper fi, soldier.
Semper fi,

1045
01:24:03,063 --> 01:24:05,585
Sic transit gloria.

1046
01:24:05,673 --> 01:24:07,631
Maybe we'll meet again someday -

1047
01:24:07,673 --> 01:24:10,544
- when the fighting stops.

1048
01:24:13,414 --> 01:24:16,414
Tag 'em and bag 'em, cherries!
We're movin' out!

1049
01:24:31,896 --> 01:24:33,852
Hello, Esposito.

1050
01:24:38,201 --> 01:24:40,115
Will you marry me, Le-Chahn?

1051
01:24:41,680 --> 01:24:43,637
You bet I will.

1052
01:24:57,769 --> 01:25:01,509
That's my son.
That's my Maxie.

1053
01:25:10,163 --> 01:25:12,989
I just didn't expect to see you here.

1054
01:25:13,077 --> 01:25:15,077
Did Max send you an invitation?

1055
01:25:15,165 --> 01:25:18,512
Yeah, and he told me to wear a tie.

1056
01:25:20,339 --> 01:25:24,602
- Congratulations, Max.
- Thank you very much, Mrs. Yang.

1057
01:25:24,688 --> 01:25:27,775
I, uh, actually wrote a different
version of the play two years ago, -

1058
01:25:27,863 --> 01:25:29,776
- but I couldn't get it done
over at Rushmore.

1059
01:25:29,862 --> 01:25:32,124
- Oh, really? Why?
- Too political?

1060
01:25:32,210 --> 01:25:35,168
No, a kid got his finger blown off
during rehearsals.

1061
01:25:35,254 --> 01:25:38,169
A very good evening
to you, Fischers. Hi.

1062
01:25:38,256 --> 01:25:40,691
Miss Cross, I'd like for you
to meet my father, Bert Fischer.

1063
01:25:40,778 --> 01:25:43,865
He's a barber.
This is my friend, Rosemary Cross.

1064
01:25:43,952 --> 01:25:46,692
- Hello, Rosemary.
- Nice to meet you at last, Bert.

1065
01:25:46,779 --> 01:25:48,693
Of course you know Mr. Blume.

1066
01:25:48,779 --> 01:25:53,085
I'd also like everyone to meet
Mr. And Mrs. Yang. This is Margaret.

1067
01:25:53,171 --> 01:25:55,911
- Hello, Margaret.
- It's nice to meet you, Miss Cross.

1068
01:25:55,998 --> 01:25:58,216
I'm surprised they let him build
a real campfire on the stage.

1069
01:25:58,304 --> 01:26:00,217
It's clearly a safety hazard.

1070
01:26:00,303 --> 01:26:02,173
